				<h2>Answer</h2>
				<h3>Score ::-1</h3>
				<p><p>I agree in theory with @JasonSalaz's solution <a href="https://apple.stackexchange.com/questions/tagged/ibooks" class="post-tag" title="show questions tagged &#39;ibooks&#39;" rel="tag">ibooks</a> for the app and <a href="https://apple.stackexchange.com/questions/tagged/ibook" class="post-tag" title="show questions tagged &#39;ibook&#39;" rel="tag">ibook</a> for the hardware.</p>

<p>Hopwever I think that users will not read the wiki and will carry on misusing the tags.</p>

<p>I think as iBook is now an old machine that a better solution would be to make the tag for the machine to be <a href="https://apple.stackexchange.com/questions/tagged/ibook-laptop" class="post-tag" title="show questions tagged &#39;ibook-laptop&#39;" rel="tag">ibook-laptop</a> and remove an not allow [tag:iBook to be used]. Even then I would not be suprised to see machine related questions being wrongly tagged but this way would lead to the least errors.</p>
</p><br>
